  "text": "The number of EPSPs evoked for up to 5 s following tail shock also decreased significantly with age (p ≤ 0.001; n = 21 for M, n = 27 for O). * * and * * * denote significant difference from mature at p ≤ 0.01 and p ≤ 0.001, respectively. The physiological role of L-Glu and D-Asp excitatory responses in PVC and BSC sensory neurons is undemonstrated. Sensorimotor synapses of these cells are vulnerable to synaptic facilitation and depression [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , thus excitatory agonists including L-Glu and DAsp may serve as neuromodulators. iGluR subunits have been localized to nerve terminals in peripheral tissues served by sensory afferents [CITATION_3] . Administration of L-Glu to peripheral sensory axons resulted in nociceptive behaviors including a significant elevation of rat paw withdrawal scores following mechanical stimulation [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . L-GluR agonists may stimulate sensory PVC neurons to serve a similar nociceptive role in the Aplysia nervous system.",
